parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key will not turn
the ignition switch is hot
the vehicle will not start
the theft system light is on
the dashboard lights flash erratically.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle's lights, gauges, and other systems to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The headlights flicker or go out
the dashboard lights flash erratically
the gauges on the instrument panel do not work
the vehicle's battery drains
the interior lights flash while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle accelerates without pressing the gas pedal
the vehicle jerks or hesitates while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the interior and exterior lighting can cause visibility problems, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The headlights flicker or go out
the interior lights flash while driving
the dashboard lights flash erratically
the brake lights do not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling and failure can cause loss of power, loss of control, and accidents, leading to serious safety risks.
symptoms: The engine stalls while driving
often without warning
and may not restart; the vehicle may jerk or hesitate while driving; the "check engine" light may come on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cooling system failure can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage, stalling, and loss of control, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: The engine overheats
often without warning; the temperature gauge may rise rapidly; the vehicle may stall or lose power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system failure can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and accidents, leading to serious safety risks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause loss of power, loss of control, and accidents, leading to serious safety risks.
symptoms: The headlights or other lights may malfunction or flash; the vehicle may stall or lose power; the "check engine" light may come on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause loss of power, loss of control, and accidents, leading to serious safety risks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intake valve failure can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and accidents, leading to serious safety risks.
